               <h1><center>Illustrating Economic Indicators: Visualizing the Global Economy in Recent Years</center></h1> 
               <br>
               <h6>Indicators utilized in the visualizations consist of Gross Domestic Product to track a nation's wealth, Consumer Price Index growth to measure inflation, global unemployment rates, Official Developmental Assistance metrics to monitor global aid, and the Human Development Index to quantify nation "development".</h6>
                  <br>
                  <p class="font-italic">
                  The data may be found among the tables <a style="color: lightseagreen" href="http://wdi.worldbank.org/tables" target="_blank">here</a>. Thank you World Bank!
             </p>
         </div>

