                     <div class="col-2"></div>
                        <div class="col-8">
                           <br>
                           <br>
                           <p>Here we have the aid per capita received by each country. The interesting part about these is how although Sub-Saharan Africa received substantially more aid than the other regions, when it comes to the per capita, other areas are on par with East Asia being even higher. This implies two things. 
                              <br><br>
                              The first thing is the major impact population size can have on individuals receiving aid. 
                              <br><br>
                              The second thing is that some form of disaster likely hit in 2015 and 2016 which specifically battered many of the Asian island nations. Sure enough, this two year span had its fair share of tsunamis and other natural disasters.
                              </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-2">
